>NAME

setuid - set user IDs

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <sys/types.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	
	int setuid(uid_t 'uid');

>DESCRIPTION

This function changes user IDs. If the current effective user ID is 0 ('root'), then 'uid' can have any value, and the effective, saved, and real user IDs are all set to 'uid'. Otherwise, 'uid' must be the current effective or real user ID, and the effective user ID is changed to 'uid'.

>RETURN VALUE

This function returns '0' on success, or '-1' on error and sets [errno.6] appropriately.

>ERRORS

On error, this function returns '-1' and sets [errno.6] to one of the following values:

\* *EPERM* - the current effective user ID is nonzero and 'uid' does not match the current effective or real user ID.

